reporter_caption.center: ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND v. CACERES, 392 Md. 562 (2006)

caption.center: ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND, Petitioner, v. Carlos H.

docket.center: Misc. Docket AG No. 8, September Term, 2006.

opinion.opinion_text:
ORDER Upon consideration of the Joint Petition for Disbarment by Consent filed herein pursuant to Maryland Rule 16-772, it is this 8th day of May, 2006,Page 563
ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that Carlos H. Caceres, be, and is hereby, disbarred by consent from the further practice of law in the State of Maryland; and it is further,
ORDERED, that the Clerk of this Court shall strike the name of Carlos H. Caceres from the register of attorneys, and pursuant to Maryland Rule 16-772(d) shall certify that to the Trustees of the Client Protection Fund and the Clerks of all judicial tribunals in this State.
